node.text: Join my page and get daily market news and investment plans.
Day start with the mediation of 1 hour in morning
Then the office meetings are scheduled to be cleared...
Start the day with a morning run, shower, breakfast and then you are at work for the day
Waking slowly undersunlight... Then kissing my wife which I don't have right now.... Then hot water tub and shower.... Then running in garden ....
Tell us routine of your boss i.e. Mr Mukesh Ambani and we'll tell you ours üòÇüòÇ

Try to squeeze in a run before sitting on my desk. But it's extremely rare, since news never stops. But I do have a cup of tea by myself in my balcony garden before my morning meetings start. Then scout for big news of the day on my mobile üòÖ
Aaye 10 baj gaye. Jaldi utho aur connect karo meeting haiüòÇ
Pet dekhte rahte hai bss kab kam hoga
Waking up at 9:25 to attend zoom call at 9:30 a.m. and working 9:30-9:30, 12 hours ka job ü§™ü§£ uske baad din shuru hota hü•∫
Waking up at 7am_geeting fresh_take breakfast_watch global market_make treding plan_than light exercise or meditation execution of treding plan_making profit/loss.üî•
Outlook pe delay delivery Login mail raat ko hi daal ke rakhte hai.... Aur subah aaram se uth ke kaam par baithte hai üòâ
Protein shake then right to the office!
Cup of steaming masala tea and overnight mails üòÄ
By opening my Demat account and checking last day's Trading contract note.

Como ya sab√©is nos encanta reutilizar objetos que han perdido su utilidad, pero que formalmente todav√≠a evocan mucho. En esta ocasi√≥n hemos cogido un elemento que se ha vuelto muy cotidiano en nuestras vidas como son las mascarillas.

Para nosotros las mascarillas son peque√±os caparazones que nos protegen del maldito COVID-19, y eso fue lo que nos inspir√≥ a convertirlos en peque√±as tortugas de papel.

Para nosotros, es una de las ideas m√°s bonitas que hemos tenido porque en ella se mezcla el reciclaje y las esculturas hechas en papel, dos conceptos que representan muy bien lo que es Panel Cero.

Esperamos que os guste.

shortcode_media.accessibility_caption:
Video by Institute for Creative Arts in Institute for Creative Arts - ICA. BIG NEWS ‼Ô∏è

The ICA invited applications for an Online Fellowship Programme designed to help artists develop and realise their interdisciplinary artistic work online. The Programme was launched in response to the devastation wrought on our health and economies, and especially on artists, by #COVID-19 as well as to the possibilities that crisis might offer for the development of new forms and new ways of seeing and experiencing art. 

We received 218 applications! Based on the high calibre of submissions, we extended the numbers of Fellows from 20 (as initially advertised) to 34.

The 34 selected fellows will now collaborate with the curatorial and project team at the ICA, and other members of staff across Faculties at the University of Cape Town, as well as digital interaction designers to develop a plan and a rendering for the online showing of their work. This will finally take the form of a live art or interdisciplinary work using music, theatre, dance or fine art as a base, and collaborating across disciplines. 

#ICAOnline

Rains have been wreaking havoc across north India with many rivers flowing close to the danger mark.

In the national capital, the Yamuna was flowing near the warning mark on Wednesday and is likely to swell further with more water being released into it from the Hathnikund barrage in Haryana, officials said.

In Uttar Pradesh, the number of districts hit by floods went up to 19 with Shahjahanpur being added to the list.

“There are 19 flood-affected districts, where 922 villages are affected, of which 571 are marooned,” state Relief Commissioner Sanjay Goel said. Till Tuesday, 1,090 villages across 18 districts were affected. Of these, 620 villages had got marooned.

Dr Roy said that making sure the pandemic does not spread among the archipelago's other indigenous tribes was now a main priority.

"We are keeping a close watch on movements and mass testing some of the tribes," he said.

The Andamans is home to five vulnerable tribes: the Jarawas, North Sentinelese, Great Andamanese, Onge and Shompen.

node.text: Currently situation for Queensland, there’s been a testing site set up at my local shopping centre due to the recent covid cases that have occurred. For those who have been concerned with regards of someone with covid attending a @tafeqld campus just thought that I would let you all know that I attend the Mount Gravatt campus and that it was at the Springfield campus where it happened. So everyone who is at my campus are all fine and you have nothing to worry about. I do find it scary that the person went to the nail that is opposite of where my skin clinic is. I go to the @brisbane.antiwrinkle.studios to get laser hair removal done on my face and so far I haven’t heard how they are there or what’s happened but I’m sure they are fine as no news is good news. Please for those who are concerned don’t be afraid to DM me or comment below and I’ll let you guys know that I’m ok. I am at high risk due to having sleep apnoea and I really have to be on the alert too. #covid19 #covid #coronavirus #stopthespreadofcovid19 #stopthespread #stayathome #qldhealth #queenslandhealth

Climate Change is real but many people think it is not that big a deal. The problem is more severe and impactful than it sounds because the figures suggest that Earth may yeild the most habitable environment for humans to live on it. India being the 7th largest country on this planet is no exception to this phenomenom. The figures states in this post paints a clear picutre of how climate change has affected Indian Region over the years and the future of it.
.

üåªNursery Mummasüåª

I had the pleasure of working in our special care nursery this week ü§±
I don’t know if it’s just because I’ve been thinking üí≠ about it more lately, or if it’s you guys, but it struck me just how hard it could be, to have your babe in the nursery when you are at home üè†

The emotions, the hormones going crazy through you at the time, your supply is coming in... you’re up in the night üåì expressing even though your baby isn’t there, you come in for visits, and sometimes aren’t even allowed to hold your baby. ü§±

I can’t begin to imagine how hard it must be in countries where #COVID is is crazy üò¢

All I can say to you is... YOU ARE AMAZING! We are often told as midwives that the work we so is amazing, but I believe that it’s really the MUMS that are the incredible ones.  The ones who work hard to feed their babe, to care for them and visit them and hold and comfort them! üåø 

Mums are incredible and for all of you with babies in the #NICU, this is an appreciation post for you üíõ Keep I’m fighting üí™üèª

shortcode_media.accessibility_caption: Photo by kesehatan on August 27, 2020. Image may contain: 1 person, text that says 'Proud Indonesia #medik alnesia MEDIA KESEHATAN INDONESIA ‡∂ö‡∂≠‡∂±‡∑ä‡∑Ç‡∂ö‡∂≠‡∂Ω Kenapa Pemain Sepakbola Meludah Kembali Setelah Minum? Ini Penjelasannya!'.

node.text:
Mungkin sebagian dari kita masih bertanya-tanya, saat menyaksikan pertandingan sepakbola di televisi, kita sering kali melihat pemain sepakbola minum air dari botol tetapi kemudian meludahkannya kembali.

Dan ternyata, menurut para ilmuwan nutrisi yang dikutip oleh New York Times . Itu adalah trik untuk menipu otak agar mendapatkan rangsangan pada otot yang kelelahan.

Ketika air memenuhi mulut, maka yang terjadi adalah reseptor mulut dirangsang mendeteksi beberapa jenis karbohidrat dan mengirim sinyal "kegembiraan" ke pusat-pusat kesenangan otak.

Persepsinya adalah akan ada lebih banyak energi dalam meredakan stres dan membuat otot bekerja lebih banyak tanpa melelahkan atlet.

Dan semakin lama cairan berada di dalam mulut, semakin besar kontak dengan reseptor oral dan semakin baik hasilnya. Jangan menelannya, karena itu akan mempengaruhi kinerja dengan gangguan pencernaan.

Nah. Itulah kenapa para pemain sepakbola terlihat sering meludahkan kembali saat mereka minum, mereka hanya membilas mulut untuk memanipulasi otak, tidak meminumnya, karena bisa mempengaruhi kinerja.
.
.
.
@medikalnesia

Tourism is entering a great crisis due to the worldwide panic of the Corona Virus, duration and scope still unknown, which is leading to the stock market crash continued for a week to all the giants of the sector. The impact of the Covid-19 Corona Virus on world tourism is unquestionable, and the authorities' forecasts are based on previous experiences with similar crises such as that of SARS or H1N1.

China’s tourism industry will be most affected due to the virus since tourism represents 11% of their GDP in recent years, growing in a steady rate of 7%. The¬†World Tourism Organization¬†(UNWTO) and the World Health Organization (WHO) through a joint statement have asked the tourism sector that their response to the outbreak of the Corona Virus be "measured, consistent and proportionate" to the threat posed for public health. Closing borders, prohibiting travel in general and more extreme government policies will not stop the spread of the Corona Virus, said the World Travel and Tourism Council (WTTC)..

node.text:
I’m so pleased to have been able to take part in the amazing #theoffcutproject by @theprintblock 

Loads of artists submitted work which represented how they felt about the pandemic and lockdown, these were printed in limited editions (14 prints) and are for sale at @theprintblock (details in profile).

Not only is this a fascinating and varied collection of work but ¬£10 from the sale of every print goes to food banks  via the @trusselltrust - over ¬£6000 has been raised to date! 

My submission is a quote from Twin Peaks. A gentle reminder to appreciate the small, easy to achieve pleasures was pretty key to me not entirely losing my mind many times over the past few months. 

These and more amazing prints are available for one more week only so if you want to grab a bit of artwork, and do some good pop over to https://www.theprintblock.com/photo_16681000.html

. 
. 
Kami satukan layanan perusahaan jasa pengiriman barang indonesia kedalam satu platfom digital sehingga menciptakan peluang bisnis baru.
. 
. 
RAJA EXPEDISI dilahirkan untuk menjawab panggilan perkembangan bisnis online dan kebutuhan akan jasa pengiriman barang logistik yang terus meningkat dengan signifikan dari tahun ke tahun.
.

.

node.text:
Siapa yang pernah menikmati kelezatan semangkuk soto tangkar? 

Sajian khas Betawi ini memang cukup populer di tanah Jakarta. Kuah santan dengan isian seperti paru, kikil, tulang, dimasak dengan menggunakan kayu bakar.

Salah satu rumah makan legendaris yang berhasil melestarikan soto tangkar adalah Soto Tangkar Tanah Tinggi yang telah berdiri sejak tahun 1946.

@sototangkar_tanahtinggi3 
Jalan Tanah Tinggi III No. 54, 
Senen, Jakarta Pusat.

node.text:
SPEECH PATHOLOGY WEEK - 23 - 29 AUGUST - COMMUNICATING WITH CONFIDENCE⁠
⁠
The coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic has highlighted the challenges faced by Australians with communication disability. Communication is a basic human right and Speech Pathology Week seeks to make Australians aware of this.⁠
⁠
There are 1.2 million Australians with communication disability.⁠
⁠
Every day speech pathologists work with these Australians to provide them with the confidence to communicate.⁠
⁠
Communication disability is largely invisible - unseen and out-of-sight.⁠
⁠
Communication disability takes many forms. It may be present at birth (e.g. cerebral palsy, hearing impairments and cleft palate), occur as a result of physical, intellectual or sensory disability or a mental illness, emerge during early childhood (e.g. stuttering) or during adult years (e.g. stroke, neck/head cancers), or develop in the elderly (e.g. dementia, Parkinson’s disease).⁠
⁠
If you, or someone you love, is having communication problems, please speak with your doctor so that we can help you arrange the help you need.⁠
⁠
#SPWeek⁠
⁠

node.text:
Pada rapat koordinator (rakor)kesiapan Pilkada Serentak Tahun 2020 dan Pengarahan Kepada Satuan Gugus Tugas di Provinsi Jambi, Menteri Dalam Negeri Indonesia Tito Karnavian mengingatkan pelaksanaan demokrasi itu tidak boleh terlepas dari protokol kesehatan. Dalam rakor tersebut, Tito juga mengingatkan peran Pilkada sebagai momentum untuk dapat menekan laju penyebaran Covid-19.
*
"Kita jadikan pilkada ini momentum juga untuk bisa mengendalikan (dan) menekan penyebaran Covid-19. Kenapa? (karena) Penyebaran Covid-19 kalau hanya oleh pemerintah pusat saja tidak akan bisa maksimal. 50 Persen gasnya. 270 Daerah ini (yang ikut Pilkada serentak) bisa men-trigger daerah-daerah lain, 278 daerah yang tidak ada pilkada," kata Tito, Rabu (26/8).
*
"Tetapi sebagian besar daerah-daerah yang ada pilgubnya, itu juga ada geliat pilkada. Nah ini kita harapkan ada setting tersendiri untuk penanganan ini. Yang pertama tentunya harus ada proteksi. Proteksi untuk penyelenggara, pengawas, pengaman, dan pemilih, empat-empatnya harus diberikan proteksi," imbuhnya.
*
Selengkapnya baca di www.inionline.id
*

node.text:
Terima kasih kepada Inul Vista sudah mempercayakan kepada kami untuk disterilkan

GOOD KILLS memiliki berbagai Kelebihan , diantaranya :

1. Menggunakan Mesin khusus Interior dan Eksterior yang dibedakan.
2. Menggunakan Mesin Interior dengan Techno Ultrasonic Ocean 
3. Bahan Perabotan yg membutuhkan Sterilisasi secara Khusus,  kita menggunakan Hot Steam Cleaner.
4. Menggunakan Liquid Desinfektan yg Go-Green (Ramah Lingkungan dan Manusia)
5. Desinfektan GOOD KILLS  tidak bau seperti Fogging secara umum, namun beraromatherapy yang aman untuk Manusia.
6. Hasil Detail dan Tidak meninggalkan bekas pada permukaan yang di sterilkan. Tanpa noda.
7. Efektif membunuh Kuman, Virus dan Bakteri hanya hitungan detik, dikarenakan menggunakan mesin khusus.
8. Proses pengerjaan relatif cepat dan merata hingga seluruh bagian Rumah/Kantor.
9. Proses reservasi cepat dan siap datang kerumah sesuai jadwal yang disepakati (by Request). Terima beres dan bersih sehingga client tidak perlu repot.
10. Berpengalaman dan Terpercaya sudah berbagai jenis tempat yang menggunakan Jasa Kami, testimony dapat dilihat pada @goodkill.tarakan di highlight.

Dapatkan layanan kami dengan menghubungi admin @goodkills.tarakan .
PROTEKSI DIRI bisa menggunakan Masker, Handsanitizer, Multivitamin maupun penerapan Physical Distance.

PROTEKSI LINGKUNGAN satu2nya dengan sterilisasi dengan Desinfektan secara merata pada tempat tinggal/usaha Anda.

Jangan sampai #StayAtHome namun HOME kita tidak STERIL dan ter-PROTEKSI.

La alimentaci√≥n de los ni√±os y adolescentes est√° basada en los mismos principios que la nutrici√≥n de los adultos. Las personas necesitamos los mismos tipos de nutrientes. Las cantidades de esos nutrientes dependen de muchos factores personales, como edad, actividad f√≠sica, estatura, peso, enfermedades existentes, #alergias, #intolerancias, entre otros.

Se realiz√≥ una investigaci√≥n¬† para determinar la percepcioÃÅn que tienen los padres sobre los #haÃÅbitos nutricionales de sus hijos. 
Los resultados dijeron que una cantidad importante de padres no tiene conciencia de los¬† malos h√°bitos de alimentaci√≥n de sus hijos. 
Por ejemplo el 82,8% de los escolares espanÃÉoles no desayunan bien. 
El 93,1% de los #escolares encuestados no duermen las horas diarias recomendadas. 
El 45,7% dedica como mucho dos horas a la semana a #actividadefiÃÅsica extraescolar. 
El 71% comen al tiempo que ven la televisi√≥n o usan aparatos electr√≥nicos. 
El 35,2 % de los padres no acuden a un especialista para informarse de los haÃÅbitos de alimentacioÃÅn saludable. 

Debe asegurase que la alimentaci√≥n de #ni√±os y #adolescentes incluya una variedad de alimentos de los principales grupos: frutas, verduras, cereales integrales, productos l√°cteos bajos en grasa, prote√≠nas magras, incluyendo legumbres, frutos secos y grasas saludables. 
La buena nutrici√≥n se garantiza si se consumen alimentos frescos y sin procesar. Si un ni√±o o adolescente consume alimentos con alto contenido cal√≥rico, como comidas r√°pidas, productos procesados, golosinas, boller√≠a, bebidas azucaradas , puede presentar #malnutrici√≥n y con el paso del tiempo enfermedades asociadas a la alimentaci√≥n, como #hipertensi√≥n arterial, #diabetes, #hiperlipidemia, #enfermedadesdigestivas. 

Modificar la alimentaci√≥n con una #dietaequilibrada adaptada a sus requerimientos personales, garantiza un adecuado crecimiento y desarrollo y les ayuda a mantener su sistema inmunitario en buen estado para hacer frente a enfermedades.

node.text: @so.bios Are you basing your lack of choice over a deterministic argument? If so, then even your death will remain a pre determined phenomenon. If not,then I believe your freedom of choice is limited to how you define it for yourself

I’m gonna kill myself one day. Maybe 10 years later, maybe on my 69th birthday. 
Not just because I hate existence but because nothing’s ever been my own choice, let death be mine.

@ishaan_pant and at the same time go with a "bang". What I mean to say is, that I believe that Suicide in itself is a way people gain meaning for their lives. "ikigai" refers to a meaning of life which we find for ourselves

@ishaan_pant Cioran's quote on suicide, "If I didn't have the option of suicide I'd kill myself" reflects on the same aspect. People kill themselves for various reasons, for instance - a bad job, bad relationships etc. Death is greater than all these issues, and the fact that I can always kill myself means that there is no need for me to worry over these trivial matters or think of suicide. From there, I find that suicide is a form of self expression, a rebellion of sorts. But what good is a rebellion which is crushed? If I kill myself now, but instead of MY reasons for committing suicide, the virus is glorified then what form of a self expression is this? Apologises for the slight incoherence
@ishaan_pant thats a whole different point of view. Thank you, i think about it for a moment
How is this post tagged with the hashtag 'suicideprevention'???
No wonder suicide rates go down every epidemic

node.text:
The University of Cambridge on Wednesday confirmed plans to begin trials of a potential new vaccine not only against COVID-19 but all coronaviruses that may spill over from animals to humans in the future.

The new vaccine candidate, DIOS-CoVax2, uses banks of genetic sequences of all known coronaviruses, including those from bats, believed to be the natural hosts of many relatives of human coronaviruses. A vaccine that clears all trials can then be delivered pain-free without a needle into the skin through a spring-powered jet injection.

node.text:
Four prisoners undergoing treatment for Covid-19 at Gandhi Hospital have escaped from the prisoner’s ward on Thursday.

Police said that the four offenders, who have been referred to Gandhi Hospital from Cherlapalli central prison and Government Hospital for Mental Care in Erragadda, have bent the iron rods of toilet window in the prisoner’s ward and climbed down using a rope made of curtains.

The incident happened during the early hours of Thursday, and special teams have launched a manhunt to zero in on the fugitives.
.
